Package com.castsoftware.exporter.exceptions.file

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    FileCorruptedException
    The FileNotFound is thrown when the procedure can't read a file because of corrupted file or bad format.
    FileIOException
    The FileNotFound is thrown when the procedure can't access a file because it doesn't exist, or the path resolution failed.
    FileNotFoundException
    The FileNotFound is thrown when the procedure can't access a file because it doesn't exist, or the path resolution failed.
    FilePermissionException
    The FilePermissionError is thrown when the procedure can't access a file because it doesn't have the require permissions.
